      <intermediateExchange id="5e1048e3-43d2-5f05-8290-50d817423c72" unitId="5b972631-34e3-4db7-a615-f6931770a0cb" amount="4E-10" intermediateExchangeId="3d0fe4e0-eac9-4704-b3fd-09b8594d0fbe" activityLinkId="d9966a8a-179d-5f90-b936-aa62beea7899">
        <name xml:lang="en">chemical factory, organics</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">unit</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Location=RER
No information was readily available about infrastructure and land-use of p-nitrophenol production plants. Therefore, in this study, the infrastructure is estimated based on the module "chemical plant, organics". This module assumes a built area of about 4.2 ha, an average output of 50'000 t/a, and plant life of fifty years. For this study, the estimated value is 4.00 E-10 units per kg of produced chemical.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="4E-10" mu="-21.639556568820566" variance="0.1404" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.3184"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="4" completeness="5" temporalCorrelation="5" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="5"/>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Estimation</comment>
        </uncertainty>
